The paper discusses the use of cloud and mobile computing for resource management, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of a centralised controller for managing resources, which is a common approach in distributed systems (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of auto-scaling, which is a common technique in cloud computing (cs.Distributed). The paper also discusses the use of a protocol for managing resources, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobile devices, which could fall under the category of augmented reality (cs.AR).
